<item>
            <title>[LU-12149] Newly formatted MGT reports error on mount</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12149</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A freshly created MGT reports the following after mounting:&lt;br/&gt;
 hoeplustre06-mgs-mds-n1 kernel: Lustre: 371323:0:(osd_handler.c:7070:osd_mount()) MGS-osd: device /dev/mapper/vg_mgs-mgs was upgraded from Lustre-1.x without enabling the dirdata feature. If you do not want to downgrade to Lustre-1.x again, you can enable it via &apos;tune2fs -O dirdata device&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My understanding is that dhrdata is not required on the MGT so the check should be removed for MGT devices or it should be set when running mkfs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
